
ANSI Color Sequences for use with ansi_notify and {ansi:msg,player}

Effects:
^NORMAL^   ^FLASH^    ^INVERT^   ^ ^      ( ^ ^ is the same as ^NORMAL^ )

Dark:
^BLACK^    ^CRIMSON^  ^FOREST^   ^BROWN^
^NAVY^     ^VIOLET^   ^AQUA^     ^GRAY^

Light:
^GLOOM^    ^RED^      ^GREEN^    ^YELLOW^
^BLUE^     ^PURPLE^   ^CYAN^     ^WHITE^

Background:
^BBLACK^   ^BRED^     ^BGREEN^   ^BBROWN^
^BBLUE^    ^BPURPLE^  ^BCYAN^    ^BGRAY^

*Note, to have colored forgrounds on backgrounds, set the color first:
^BLUE^^BGRAY^
Setting a foreground color resets the background color to black.
Flash and Invert can be set before or after colors and/or background colors.
Two ^^s will produce one ^ in text.
